# Feature 6 verifier audit log — Checklists, paired chats, auto-driver

Started: 2026-05-07T20:17:34-05:00


## Findings cross-referenced against HEAD

### F1 (Critical) — Blocking followups don't recurse
- Cited path: `auto_driver.py:501-507`
- HEAD: `src/bearings/agent/auto_driver.py:499-507` — `_apply_followups` calls
  `checklists_db.create(...parent_item_id=item.id)` on FOLLOWUP_BLOCKING and
  returns. No recursion — the calling leg loop continues after the followup
  insertion. `_drive_item` does not pause the parent or drive the child to
  terminal before resuming.
- Spec: `docs/behavior/checklists.md:70-71` — "A new child item is appended
  under the current item. The driver recurses into the child before
  completing the parent."
- Verdict: **STILL_OPEN**

### F2 (Critical) — Checklist auto-close cascade missing
- Cited path: `routes/checklists.py:278-287`
- HEAD: `src/bearings/web/routes/checklists.py:278-287` — `check_item` only
  calls `checklists_db.mark_checked` and returns the item. No paired-chat
  close, no parent walk, no auto-close of the checklist session.
  `db/checklists.py:396-419` `mark_checked` is also a single UPDATE — no
  cascade.
- Spec: `docs/behavior/checklists.md:47` — "Checking a paired item closes
  the chat. ... cascades up: each parent whose children are all complete
  auto-closes, and the parent checklist session auto-closes when every
  root item is complete."
- Verdict: **STILL_OPEN**

### F3 (Critical) — Chat deletion does not clear item pointer
- HEAD: `src/bearings/db/schema.sql:307` — `FOREIGN KEY (chat_session_id)
  REFERENCES sessions(id) ON DELETE SET NULL`. `db/connection.py:79`
  enables `PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON` on every connection. `db/sessions.py
  :1020-1039` `delete()` uses the bootstrapped connection so the FK
  fires; the docstring there explicitly cites the contract.
- The schema FK was present from item 0.4 (commit `0e92965d`,
  2026-04-28), well before the 2026-05-07 audit. Audit appears to have
  missed the FK constraint.
- Verdict: **FIXED_SINCE_AUDIT** (technically: never broken in HEAD;
  resolving commit pre-dates audit).

