### F6 (Medium) — Followup label not validated; whitespace labels create invalid items
- HEAD: `src/bearings/db/checklists.py:91-100` `__post_init__` only checks
  `if not self.label:` — `"   "` is truthy and slips through. Auto-driver
  `_apply_followups` (`auto_driver.py:499-514`) only checks `and label`
  (truthy), no `.strip()` discipline.
- Verdict: **STILL_OPEN**

### F7 (Medium) — No recovery if leg session vanishes mid-run
- HEAD: `src/bearings/agent/auto_driver.py:_run_leg_turns` calls
  `runtime.run_turn` without a try/except for session-vanished failure.
  `auto_driver_runtime.py:121-126` `run_turn` raises out of
  `runner_factory` if the session is gone — propagates to `drive()`
  which has `except StopRequested:` only. Any other exception escapes
  the registry's done-callback as an unhandled task error.
- Verdict: **STILL_OPEN**

### F8 (Medium) — Sidebar does not push leg-cutover events
- HEAD: `auto_driver.py:_drive_item` calls `runtime.teardown_leg`
  (`auto_driver_runtime.py:128-136`) which only drops a pressure-cache
  entry. No `publish_upsert(closed_at=…)` for the predecessor leg, no
  close on the chat session at handoff. New legs DO broadcast (via
  `web/app.py:197 _leg_session_factory` → `publish_upsert`), but the
  predecessor chat row stays "open" — the user sees rows accumulate,
  not "fast-cycle".
- Spec: `docs/behavior/checklists.md:69` "the previous chat closes,
  a fresh one opens against the same item"; line 121 "fast-cycling
  sequence of new chat rows".
- Verdict: **STILL_OPEN**

